<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-004-337 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 572 460</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Shopper  Dec 1991 v11 n12 p193(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MoneyCounts 6.5. (Parsons Technology Inc.'s financial software)(Software Review) (Best Buys of 1991) (Evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Harvey, David A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Parsons Technology Inc's MoneyCounts 6.5 financial software, a'best buy for 1991,' costs only $35 and manages finances from asingle checkbook to small business bookkeeping.andP;  MoneyCountsdisplays data in reports, charts and three-dimensional graphs;prints checks; tracks transactions; manages multiple andsubaccounts; and estimates taxes, mortgages and payments.andP;  Theanticipated MoneyCounts 7.0 will give all of these features andmore.andP;  The menu obviates the need to refer to documentation whenusing MoneyCounts, but the manual is well-written and clearlydocumented.andP;  The user does not need a background in bookkeeping,in spite of the double-entry structure of the program core.andO;Entering a transaction prompts an account that can be customizedor selected from the menu.andP;  For information that is recurring,such as monthly transactions, data need only be entered once.andO;MoneyCounts also has a built-in calculator, financial calculator,tax estimator, notepad, and data base of names and addresses.andO;Users can keep accounting journals and generate forms on cards andchecks with ease.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Parsons Technology Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   MoneyCounts 6.5 (Financial software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Financial SoftwareEvaluationTop Rating.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>